Mmusi Maimane addresses a press conference as John Steenhuisena listens on in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - Former Democratic Alliance leader Mmusi Maimane has referred to Interim DA Leader John Steenhuisen as "Judas". The jibe was in response to Steenhuisen's assertion that under Maimane the DA focused too much on bashing the ANC. READ: President should concentrate on pleasing public: analyst Steenhuisen said this at the start of his Real State of the Nation tour. Maimane retaliated saying that Steenhuisen was in full agreement with all the decisions taken by the party. Steenhuisen is yet to respond.